  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lao People&apos;s Democratic Republic Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM will focus effort on the return and recovery needs, health and well-being of those displaced and most affected by the flooding, particularly the villages hit by the dam collapse and subsequent flooding, and those in the 7 identified (to date) evacuation centres. Toensure a comprehensive response, IOM will include Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) information capacities to better track the people in evacuation sites and the return and/or relocation process, as well as the basic needs for services and assistance at each of these sites and the most affected villages. The operational activities will primarily becommodities driven initially, but IOM will deploy health staff includinglocal health volunteers to begin working with the communities on recovery, vector control, and health and hygiene promotion activities toprevent further disease risks.</narrative>
  </description>
